profile_positions.description:
Logica was an IT company with over 40.000 employees in 42 countries. In 2012 Logica has been taken over by CGI.
Anton Martens started in Logica as Manager Financial Services in the Netherlands with profit/loss for 2000 employees. After 2 years he was promoted to the international organisation where he fulfilled different roles:
-	Business development manager Global Finance Sector, with a focus on the 40 largest European banks;
-	Re-organizing business units in Netherlands, UK and Belgium;
-	Structuring, growing and managing the global service line Testing with more than 10.000 testers worldwide; 
-	Global Portfolio Manager responsible for all new offerings and new partnerships in all 42 countries of the company
